Introdcution to Excel Video
    What is Excel
        Popular spreadsheet software by Microsoft
        Insert, read, and manipulate data
        Relied on by businesses
    Why Excel
        Store, process, analyze, and visualize data
        Supports collaboration via shared workbooks, co-authoring, and commenting
        Templates for common tasks
    Limitations
        Features
            Opening workbooks
                Limited by available memory and system resources
            Total number of rows and columns on worksheet
                1,048,576 rows by 16,384 columns
    Key Definitions
        Workbook
            Excel file containing one or more worksheets to help organize all the data
                The file itself
        Worksheet
            Primary area often referred to as a sheet or spreadsheet
            Consists of cells organized into columns and rows
                A sheet within the file
        Cell
            Box at the intersection of the grid where a row and column meet where info is contained
        Cell Reference
            Combination of a column letter and row number that identifies a cell in the worksheet
            Top left corner
                A1
        Active Cell
            Cell being worked with, identified by a rectangular green box
        Range
            Two or more cells in a worksheet that don't necessarily have to be adjacent
        Formula
            Mathemtical equations, cell references, or functions placed within a cell
            Must start with an equal = sign
        Formula Bar
            Bar located at the top of the worksheet next to the fx label
            Used to enter or edit values/formulas

