Working with Tables Video
    Data within cells are only related by proximity to one another
    Tables
        Lets Excel know that all the data contained inside is related
        Column header row
            First row in table that contains column headings
        Body
            Where all rows of data and formulas live that relate to our columns
        Totals
            Off by default, but can be enabled to summarize all rows in a table
        Benefits
            Structured references
                Easy to read/understand
                Reference columns by name in table
                Dynamic and automically updates as data is added/removed
            Data integrity
                Built-in data validation features
                Apply rules to columns for certain data types
    Formatting Data
        Tables
            Re-size table
            Apply slicers
            Create pivot tables
            Apply style options/designs
        Cells
            Customize fonts, alignment, data types
            Apply conditional formatting
            Apply cell styles/themes
    Filtering/Sorting Data
        Filtering
            Hides data you do not currently want to analyze
            Built-in comparison operations like greater than or top N
        Sorting
            Integral part of data analysis
            Helps you quickly visualize/understand data better
            Esier to find data when you know what you're looking for
            Sort by text, numbers, dates, and times
            Sort by formatting cell color, font color, and icons

